Duel to the last blood: MP3 players against mobile phones
We will recommend how to choose
While almost every mobile phone can read MP3 files, no MP3 player can phone.
From this it is clear that it is better to buy only the phone.
Nevertheless, there are many reasons why an autonomous reader should be provided.
The choice depends entirely on the way of use and the needs of the future owner.
Maybe you'd hardly buy a expensive high-quality turntable to listen to Maxim Turbulenc's latest album.
First of all these musical products do not come out as LP and from a qualitative point of view for this there is no objective reason.
If, however, hard-rock, jazz or blues vinyls are piled on your shelves, a turntable like this at least you dream about it.
It also works with portable music, i.e. compressed music or simply MP3 format.
Here too there are the price and quality categories.
For some it may be unacceptable to spend for an 8 thousand crown reader, as well as a Pink Floyd fan may hardly digest the headphones from twenty crowns of the market.
Two extremes between which there is enough room for everyone.
The choice is wide.
The decision is the duration of the batteries.
Some high-quality music players manage to do much more than just read music, but they don't even make cell phones by mistake.
There is no other current device as universal as the mobile phone.
Next to the primary functions, phone and send text, can read music and video, record both and has a camera, sometimes better sometimes worse and maybe even browse.
And if we take into account smartphones and palm trees you will also have a miniature computer in your pocket.
It is a small miracle because no refrigerator can make the grid and no television can photograph anything.
The universality of the cell phone also brings disadvantages.
More functions you use on your mobile phone and before the indicator on your screen will require charger.
And reading music consumes a lot of energy.
Few mobile phones manage to read music for more than twelve hours, only, and much less.
In this sense, music readers (especially the simplest ones) are much more effective.
As far as economic cell phones are concerned, they cannot be counted for more than a few hours.
If you still add us, from time to time, some calls, get another charger to work for safety, this also applies to the most expensive appliances.
But you won't have this problem with an MP3 player, even the worst lasts at least 9 hours of continuous functionality with a charge.
A further problem arises when you download music to your mobile phone.
Unfortunately, only a limited part of the devices has the universal USB port and not all of them can be connected to the computer without special software.
Certainly the music can be recorded directly on the memory card, but only a few memory readers are able to do it without adapter for the minicards that are not used in mobile phones.
Readers, except some exceptions (Ipod) do not need any special software.
Just fill the device with the music via USB from your computer.
