The psychology of excessive bidding: why spend more money?
At auction, buyers are willing to spend more, to overestimate the goods.
Neurologists and researchers economists at the University of New York have been able to discover the neuro-economic bases of this well-known and seemingly irrational behavior.
According to their study on the journal Science men do not want to stay back in a race such as the eBay auction, so they are willing to pay even a higher price.
The research attempted to trace the nervous pattern of this "partita" at the level of the nervous system through experimental axes.
A group of volunteers played the lot, the other group of players participated in an auction while with the method of functional magnetic resonance (fMRI) examined the active brain areas of the people participating in the experiment.
In both games the participants could win money, but in the game of auction, in which the substantial element is to bid more than the other, the body striated under the cerebral cortex enters intensively into operation when you lose to the game.
This brain area, in addition to other functions, plays a role in the "autogratification" mechanism of the nervous system.
Therefore, according to the researchers, the rise of the price is explained by scanning the vehement reaction of the striated body.
To support their theory, economists of the research group conducted a financial tracking survey.
In this investigation, three groups tendered against a partner under different conditions.
The control group reported the actual value of the product in question and they made their bet.
To another group besides this they promised that in the case of winning they will receive another prize of $15.
The third group would have received $15 before the auction, but the members of the group would have lost their money in the event of an auction loss.
The difference between the two groups consisted in the fact that for one of them the win was stressed, while for the other the loss.
By checking the hypothesis of neurologists the members of the group who played "against loss" were willing to make higher stakes of the control group or "winner".
"These results cannot be deduced from any of the previously existing economic theories.
These so far explained the phenomena found in auctions with the joy of winning and avoiding the risk.
Only the methods of neurologic image creation have helped to solve the contradiction between the two theories, so that we have come to a third explanation" - said Andrew Schotter, professor of the Faculty of Economics of the University of New York.
Hepatitis: When to contact your doctor?
Almost half a billion people in the world suffer from chronic hepatitis B or C, whereas chronic liver diseases are mentioned in Hungary as the leading causes of death.
In Hungary, the number of hepatitis patients amounts to one hundred thousand, of which only 7000 are cared for: the reason is that many patients do not know how to be infected.
The definition of hepatitis is the collective name of contagious liver diseases caused by several viruses.
There are many similarities between the symptoms, typical are hepatitis and jaundice, but their pathogens and diseases are different from each other.
Hepatitis viruses are spread in two main forms depending on the pathogen: hepatitis A and E through the food channel (e.g. water and infected food), hepatitis B, C, D and other viruses with blood and organic liquids (sperm, vaginal loss, saliva).
Vaccination against the A and B virus is useful for travellers, against the C there is no vaccine.
Symptoms of hepatitis A appear two to three weeks after the consumption of infected foods, accompanied by general discomfort, weakness, abdominal pain and nausea.
After yellow spots are formed on the skin and white of the eyes, the faeces become clear and the urine dark, healing takes place within two to three weeks.
One million people die every year worldwide for hepatitis B, the most severe variant of the disease, which causes liver cancers and liver cirrhosis.
The main reason is, according to estimates, that only one in ten people receive pharmacological treatment.
Hepatitis C can also have very serious consequences: if it is not cured it can cause liver cirrhosis and liver tumors.
Most infected people do not know they have contracted the disease because the pathogens subdolely destroy the liver cells, in many cases the first symptoms appear after 20-30 years.
Therefore it is very important to prevent and perform regular medical tests.
This disease is much more frequent than the average in three groups: those who had a blood transfusion before 1991, drug addicts and tattoos.
In the world today, the number of people infected with chronic hepatitis C virus amounts to 200 million.
Since a routine laboratory examination also reveals the disease, it is worth talking to your family doctor when you notice any symptoms of unknown origin.
Recognized in time the disease is curable, the virus can be eliminated by the body, thus ceases the infectious power and can be prevented from the formation of tumors.
September 30 is the World Hepatitis Day, organized for the first time in 2004 worldwide by associations of patients.
The aim is to draw attention to chronic viral hepatitis, the causes of its development and the early recognition of the disease.
Who believes in God feels less pain?
According to the result of a recent investigation, religious faith functions as a species of analgesic that has made the death of Catholic martyrs more bearable.
Scientists at Oxford University have carried out an interesting experiment, examining how godly faith affects the feeling of pain, the British Telegraph reported.
In the context of the rather bizarre investigation, an electroshock was carried out with 12 Catholic believers and as many atheists, while all of them observed a painting depicting the Virgin Mary.
According to the results, Catholic believers were able to reject much of the pain.
Thanks to the exploratory technique of the human brain, it was discovered that Catholics were able to activate the part of the brain responsible for pain control.
The test is the first of a series of studies in which in addition to academics also take part scientists, philosophers and theologians of the University.
The test was carried out exactly this way: an instrument that emits discharges and passes the electroshock was connected to the left hand of the subject of the experiment.
The researchers asked the participants to focus on two paintings, the Virgin Mary painted in the XVII century by Sassoferrato and the Lady with the herd of Leonardo da Vinci painted in the XV century.
The authors of the examination hoped that the image of the Virgin Mary originated a kind of religious state among believers, while Leonardo's picture was chosen because it did not differ too much from the other and believed it to have a tranquillizing effect.
The subjects of the experiment spent half an hour in front of the MRI scanner and in this time slot received 20 electroshock in four consecutive series, while observing either the religious theme painting or the other.
Catholics have reported that the vision of the Virgin Mary made them feel "secure", as if "someone took care of" them and "they calmed down and were pervaded by peace".
Looking at the religious theme image, they accounted for 12% less pain than when they had Leonardo's work before them.
The psychologist Miguel Farias, who took part in the test himself, believes that such a result can be achieved with any image with a strong effect even for atheists, but you have to find the right image.
"We have to look for an image where they have very positive feelings, like a mother or father," said the psychologist.
The Anglican Bishop Tom Wright welcomed the search result.
"The practice of faith should change, and in many cases it can change our personality." - Wright added.
After the excellent results the question remains only if the believers are presented with the painting of a brick by Leonardo or another painter of similar caliber, what effect could it have on the control of pain?
Would the vision of a quality Virgin Mary bring better results?
