Industry prices continue to grow
National industrial sales prices in August 2008 increased by 0.1% compared to the previous month, by 12.9% compared to August 2007 - reports the Hungarian Central Statistical Institute.
The export sales prices of the industry in July 2008 were higher than 1.1%, compared to the previous year decreased by 3.9%.
As a result of the change in domestic and export prices, industrial production costs were more than 0.7% higher than in the previous month and 3.2% higher than in a year ago.
National industrial sales prices compared to the previous month increased by only 0.1%.
National sales prices in the manufacturing sector also rose to a minimum by 0.1% compared to July.
The increase in prices in August 2008 occurred in the leather and shoes processing sector (2.8%), especially bags and belts with 4.6% and the production of shoes with 2.5% monthly increase.
The high level of the price of plastic and chemical raw materials has caused a significant monthly increase (1.6%) in the product and chemical sector.
A decrease in prices in the oil processing sector (1.4%), in the production of electrical instruments and machinery (0.9%) and to a minimum extent in the woodworking sector (0.1%)
The prices of paper production, publishing and printing have not changed.
In the other sectors of the processing industry there was an increase in prices between 0.2 and 0.9%.
In the field of electricity, gas, steam and water supply, prices increased in August by 0.3% in domestic industrial sales, primarily as a result of the dominant effect of the increase in the gas price carried out by the authorities on 1 July.
Compared in 12 months, considering the domestic sales of the manufacturing industry, the biggest increases were in the oil processing sector (32.4%).
In the manufacture of metals products, the price increase was 13.2%, 11% in the production of food, beverages and tobacco, representing a significant weight.
There was a decrease in prices in the textile sector (2.5%) and in the production sectors of electrical instruments and machinery (0.3%).
In other sectors of the processing industry, the rate of price increase varied from 0.6% to 9.1%.
In total in the processing industry in the past year prices have risen by 10.2%.
The prices of the electricity, gas, steam and water supply sector exceeded 18.7% last year's prices.
In domestic sales between the target groups in the sectors, the largest increase in monthly prices occurred in August in sectors producing investment goods (0.7%).
In the sectors producing consumer goods, prices have grown by 0.3%, in the energy and subsequent use sectors prices have not changed compared to those of the previous month.
In August 2008, compared to the same month last year, the increase in higher prices was observed in the energy and subsequent use sector (16.8%).
In the sectors producing consumer goods the increase was 6.8%, for investment goods a decrease of 1.4% was measured.
The industrial export sales prices calculated in florins increased by 1.1% in August compared to the previous month, compared with 12 months decreased by 3.9%.
The Hungarian florin in the course of a month has weakened compared to the euro by 1.7%, compared to the US dollar by 7.1%, compared with August 2007 increased by 7.5% compared to the US dollar and by 15.9% compared to the US dollar.
