We must also review existing control systems, in the light of this scientific opinion, to ensure that they are fully effective and take the step with new technology."
Brussels had asked the independent Scientific Committee to examine the problem, given the large use of portable musical instruments and the increase in the number of young people exposed to noise from them.
"Scientists - the EU executive concludes - confirm that there is cause for concern and the European Commission will now examine with Member States and stakeholders what measures could be taken in order to better protect children and adolescents from noise from portable musical devices and related equipment."
