It is possible to limit this much by using solutions such as the reduction of noise levels and duration of exposure.
In its opinion, the EU Scientific Committee notes that users of portable musical equipment if they listen at high volume (more than 89 decibels) music for only 5 hours a week exceed the limits currently in force regarding the maximum permitted noise at the workplace.
Those who listen to music under such conditions for longer periods risk a permanent loss of hearing capacity after a period of 5 years.
This would concern 5-10% of the users of such devices and their number can be quantified between 2.5 and 10 million people in the EU.
